    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1891-09-15T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1891-09-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="76" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d76">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Pacheco</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Blaine</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of
                                    the United States in Guatemala and Honduras</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Guatemala</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1891-09-15">
                            <hi rend="italic">September
                                    15, 1891</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. Pacheco telegraphs text of articles 253 and 257 of the navigation and
                        marine law of Salvador, which fixes penalty on vessels leaving port without
                        clearance papers as follows: <list>
                        <item>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Art</hi>. 253. No vessel ought to set sail
                                without the license of the commandant of the port under penalty of
                                confiscation.</item>
                        <item>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Art</hi>. 257. Every infraction of the
                                articles contained in this paragraph shall he punishable by fine not
                                exceeding $200, at discretion of the commandant of the port.</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
            </div>
        </body>
